DING RUSSIAN LITERATURE IN A MULTI-NATIONAL CONTEXT.     TRADITIONALLY RUSSIAN LITERATURE HAS TACKLED THE PROBLEMS OF MINORITYNATIONALITIES, WHILE ITS WIDESPREAD DISSEMINATION HAS HELPED BOND THOSEPEOPLES TOGETHER. A RESEARCH PROJECT TO DETERMINE THE IMPACT OF RUSSIANLITERATURE TODAY ON NON-RUSSIAN PEOPLES WITHIN THE USSR WAS RECENTLYUNDERTAKEN BY THE LENIN STATE LIBRARY. THE PROJECT CONSIDERED THE AVAILABILITYOF RUSSIAN LITERATURE, THE EXTENT TO WHICH IT WAS READ AND THE VALUEATTRIBUTED TO SUCH READING. THE PROJECT IS INTENDED TO RECOMMEND TO LIBRARIESLEVELS OF PROVISION AND METHODS OF PROMOTING SUCH LITERATURE, AND THE RESEARCHMETHODS USED WILL PROVIDE A FORMAT FOR FUTURE PROJECTS